A major earthquake, lasting 15 seconds and measuring 6.5 on the Richter scale, rocked 
northern California Tuesday evening. Candlestick Park, where fans awaited start of the 
World Series, shook and was evacuated. San Francisco buildings swayed several feet and 
some collapsed. A 30-foot section of the San Francisco Bay Bridge upper deck collapsed 
onto the bottom level.  The quake shook buildings 95 miles northeast in Sacramento, and 
was felt 225 miles east in Reno, Nevada. It knocked out phones and power. The Richter 
scale measures ground motion. Every increase of one number means a tenfold increase in 
magnitude. The San Francisco earthquake of 1906 has been estimated at 8.3.</SUM> 

<SUM
DOCSET="d077"
TYPE="PERDOC"
